# Prefer the shared helpers

Before writing a "small utility" inline, check if one already exists.
Three patterns recur enough that inlining them is treated as a code smell.

## Error message extraction

Never inline `err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)`.

```ts
// BAD
log.warn("write:error", {
  error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err),
});

// GOOD
import { commonUtils } from "@dbx-tools/shared";
log.warn("write:error", { error: commonUtils.errorMessage(err) });
```

Browser-safe (re-exported from `index.client.ts`).

## Best-effort `fs.stat`

Never wrap `node:fs/promises` `stat` in try/catch for missing paths.

```ts
// BAD
try {
  if ((await stat(path)).isFile()) { ... }
} catch { ... }

// GOOD
import { fileUtils } from "@dbx-tools/shared";
const info = await fileUtils.stat(path);
if (info?.isFile()) { ... }
```

Server-only (`index.ts` entry). Returns `undefined` for empty/invalid
paths and `ENOENT`; other I/O errors propagate.

## Best-effort writer.write (appkit-mastra)

Never reinvent the "downstream stream may be closed, swallow errors"
pattern around Mastra's `ctx.writer`. Use the shared helper.

```ts
// In any file under packages/appkit-mastra/src/
import { safeWrite } from "./writer.js";

await safeWrite(log, writer, event, { chartId }); // last arg is optional log context
```

Pass the module's tagged `logUtils.logger(...)` so warnings carry the
right prefix. The helper no-ops on undefined `writer`, logs `debug` on
success, `warn` on failure, and never throws.

## Sibling-plugin lookup

Don't hand-cast `this.context.getPlugins().get("foo")`. Use
`appkitUtils.instance()` (returns `Plugin | undefined`) or
`appkitUtils.require()` (throws on missing).

```ts
import { lakebase } from "@databricks/appkit";
import { appkitUtils } from "@dbx-tools/shared";

const pool = appkitUtils.require(this.context, lakebase, "mastra").exports().pool;
```

## `@dbx-tools/appkit-config` - check before duplicating

Lakebase address parsing lives in `pgaddress.ts` only:

- `parseAddress()` for any user/env input (URIs, resource paths, hostnames, bare project ids).
- `parseResourcePath()` when the value is known to be a `projects/...` path (REST list `name` fields, bundle `POSTGRES_*` paths). Returns `{}` for bare branch ids so they are not mistaken for project ids.

Lakebase REST discovery and env application live in `lakebase-resolver.ts` (`readLakebaseInputs`, `resolveLakebaseConnection`, `applyLakebaseToEnv`). Do not add regex or path-splitting helpers there - import from `pgaddress.js`.

Env + bundle validate JSON resolution lives in `@dbx-tools/shared`
(`configUtils.resolveConfigValue`, `configUtils.findBundleRoot`). Databricks
App `config.env` flattening lives in `app-resolver.ts` (`flattenAppEnv`)
and is wired into `config-value.ts` for local dev only. Auto-pick applies
when the bundle has exactly one app; multi-app bundles require an explicit
`bundleAppEnv` key. `loadBundleConfig` skips bundle validate inside a
Databricks App (`commonUtils.isDatabricksAppEnv`). Do not hand-roll env key
normalization in either package.
